# FlashOS FAT32 permission overlay (PERMS.TAB)
#
# Format: NAME MODE UID GID
#   NAME — 8.3 basename in the FAT32 root (matched case-insensitively)
#   MODE — octal permission word (low 9 bits)
#   UID / GID — decimal owner ids
#
# Parsed once at mount time by the kernel (src/overlay.zig wired through
# src/fat32_backend.zig). Un-annotated files keep the 0666 root:root
# default; the shadow file floors at 0600 even without this overlay.
# This file protects itself through its own entry.
#
# Seeded onto the QEMU SD image by scripts/make_test_disk.sh and onto a
# real card by `zig build deploy`.
PERMS.TAB 0600 0 0
SHADOW 0600 0 0
ROUNDTR.DAT 0666 0 0
ROUNDTR.MAG 0666 0 0
